cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper focuses on confidence modeling for neural semantic parsers, which are used in natural language processing tasks such as question answering and dialogue systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses various metrics and techniques for estimating confidence scores, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the interpretation of model predictions, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
